<div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4ac ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws28">rested on the seventh day from all His works’<span class="_ _32"> </span>” <span class="ff11 ws5">(NKJV)</span>, a quote from </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4ad ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">Genesis 2:2. </div><div class="t m0 x59 h37 y4ae ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 wscb">This week we will look at various references that point back to the </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4af ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws63">Genesis account and show how other Bible writers understood it as a </div><div class="t m0 x46 h37 y4b0 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">literal depiction of human origins. </div><div class="t m0 x59 h37 y4b1 ff12 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws5"> </div><div class="t m0 x3c h34 y4b2 ff11 fs3 fc3 sc0 ls2 ws6">*Study this week’s lesson to prepare for Sabbath, January 26.</div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
